Turkish Equity Movers: Dogan Yayin, BIM, Trakya Cam Sanayi

-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 
2011-04-08T08:15:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/turkish-equity-movers-dogan-yayin-bim-trakya-cam-sanayi.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for the first day in five, losing 155.07, or 0.2
percent, to 69,335.40 at 11:02 a.m. in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  , Turkey’s biggest media
group, declined 14 kurus, or 6.9 percent, to 1.90 liras, the
biggest intraday drop in six weeks, after saying it will double
its capital to 2 billion liras ($1.3 billion) by offering rights
shares at 1 lira each.  BIM Birlesik Magazalar AS (BIMAS)  , a discount
supermarket chain, dropped 75 kurus, or 1.4 percent, to 53.50
liras after announcing it will propose to pay 182.2 million
liras ($121 million), or 1.2 liras per share, in gross dividends
from 2010 profit in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange
after the market closed yesterday.  Trakya Cam Sanayi AS (TRKCM)  , a maker of flat and
automobile glass, rose 1 kurus, or 0.3 percent, to 3.65 liras
after its price estimate was raised to 4.31 liras from 3.63
liras at Citigroup Inc., according to a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
